# Pest Risk Prediction Backend

This directory contains the backend service for the Pest Risk Prediction and Integrated Pest Management (IPM) Recommendation System developed for the EYIC Innovation Challenge.

The backend is responsible for loading trained machine learning models and providing pest risk predictions to the frontend dashboard through an API.

## Overview

The backend receives environmental and crop-related input data from the frontend application, processes the input, and generates pest risk predictions using trained machine learning models.

The system currently supports prediction for crops such as cotton and rice. Based on the model output, the backend returns a pest risk score that can be used by the dashboard to display risk levels and recommendations.

## Files

main.py  
Main API service that loads the trained models and exposes endpoints for prediction requests.

__pycache__/  
Automatically generated Python cache files.

## Functionality

The backend performs the following tasks:

1. Loads trained machine learning models stored as serialized files.
2. Accepts input data such as environmental parameters and crop conditions.
3. Processes the input features.
4. Runs the machine learning model to estimate pest risk.
5. Returns prediction results to the frontend application.

## Technologies Used

Python  
FastAPI / Flask (depending on implementation in main.py)  
Scikit-learn  
XGBoost  
Joblib / Pickle for model loading

## Running the Backend

Install dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt

Start the backend server:

python main.py

The backend will start a local API service that can be accessed by the frontend dashboard.

## Role in the System

The backend acts as the prediction engine of the system. It connects the trained machine learning models with the user interface and enables real-time pest risk assessment.
